This article discusses the significance of Columbus Day and its connection to Italian Americans. It mentions Christopher Columbus's journey in 1492 and how it remains a source of pride for many Italian Americans. The article highlights the contributions of Italian immigrants to America and their pursuit of the American dream. It acknowledges the challenges faced by Italian Americans, including prejudice and violence. The article also emphasizes the leadership and achievements of Italian Americans in various fields. It mentions the creation of Columbus Day in response to the lynching of Italian Americans in 1891 and the targeting of Italian Americans as enemy aliens during World War II. The article emphasizes the close relationship between Italy and the United States and their joint efforts to address global challenges. Finally, it proclaims October 10, 2022, as Columbus Day and calls for the display of the US flag on that day.